  "texts": [
    "Imputation was performed within the cross-validation loop, first on the training set and then on the test set using the prediction matrix developed on the training set.",
    "The standard method of dealing with categorical data in machine learning is to use one-hot encoding, whereby a new binary feature is created for each level of each categorical feature.",
    "With a large number of categorical features, such as in the MAS dataset, this can increase the dimensionality of the data enormously.",
    "Moreover, categories with levels containing only a small number of observations are usually not very predictive.",
    "In order to overcome these difficulties, alternative methods of dealing with categorical data were employed."
  ],
